# Internationalization

## No hardcoded UI strings

User-visible text must use `useTranslation(namespace)`:

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
const { t } = useTranslation("pages")
<PageHeader title={t("heroes.title")} description={t("heroes.description")} />

// ❌ BAD
<PageHeader title="Tướng" description="Danh sách tướng" />
```

Exceptions: admin-only labels in `AdminSidebar`, sample seed content, proper nouns in game data.

## Namespaces (from `src/i18n/config.ts`)

`common` · `nav` · `auth` · `footer` · `home` · `pages` · `tools` · `community` · `news`

Pick the namespace that owns the feature. Nav labels use `nav`; page copy uses `pages`.

## vi/en parity

Every key added to `src/locales/vi/*.json` must exist in the matching `src/locales/en/*.json` file (and vice versa). Run `node scripts/i18n-check.mjs` to verify.

## Nav i18n

`NAV_ITEMS` in `src/config/nav.ts` uses `labelKey` — never inline labels. Resolve via `useNavItems()` or `t("nav:home")`.

## Default locale

`DEFAULT_LOCALE` is `"vi"`. English is secondary; both must read naturally.
